This paper deals with security and performance issues related to cache memory, which is a fundamental component of computer systems. The paper discusses attacks and defenses related to cache randomization, which is a technique used to prevent timing-based side-channel attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AR (Architecture), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper also discusses performance and implementation issues related to cache memory.
